node.text:
@behind.amandaschair is serving up some inspo for your next caramel balayage. 🤩

As salon pros, we know each client's hair type and texture is as unique as they are. 👇 Make sure you consider porosity when developing their custom care regimen - save the guide below!

Low Porosity Hair:
Low porosity hair can't handle thick oils or creams. As an add-on service, offer the #WellaElements Renewing Mask for ultra-lightweight hydration and repair that won't weigh hair down.

Medium Porosity Hair:
To decide which products to use for this porosity type, think about your client's texture. Is their hair coarse or curly? Lean towards heavier moisturizing ingredients. Is their hair fine or thin? Offer some lightweight strengthening treatments!

High Porosity Hair:
This porosity type loves tons of hydration! Use the #INVIGO Nutri-Enrich line in the salon, and send clients home with the Nutri-Enrich Wonder Balm to use for a daily, powerful dose of vitamins and nourishment.

#wellahair #wellalife #wellaeducation #stylistspotlight @clairol_pro @wellahairusa
